        <h2>Password Security and Token Verification</h2>
        <p>Password Security:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Hashing:</strong> Implemented strong password hashing using bcrypt for secure storage.</li>
            <li><strong>Salting:</strong> Utilized unique and random salts for each user's password.</li>
            <li><strong>Key Stretching:</strong> Increased hashing iterations to enhance security.</li>
            <li><strong>Password Policies:</strong> Enforced complexity requirements and regular password updates.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Token Verification:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>JWT (JSON Web Tokens):</strong> Implemented secure signing algorithms and kept tokens small.
            </li>
            <li><strong>Token Expiry:</strong> Set short expiry times to limit potential misuse.</li>
            <li><strong>Token Revocation:</strong> Implemented mechanisms for token revocation and invalidation.</li>
            <li><strong>Secure Transmission:</strong> Ensured secure transmission of tokens over HTTPS.</li>
        </ul>
